# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# │       │         │
# │       │         └─⫸ Summary in present tense. Not capitalized. No period at the end.
# │       │
# │       └─⫸ Commit Scope: operator|api|ui|controllers|crd|webhooks|helm|docs|deps|security
# │
# └─⫸ Commit Type: feat|fix|docs|style|refactor|perf|test|build|ci|chore|revert
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# <body>
# Explain the motivation for the change and contrast with previous behavior.
# Use imperative mood: "change" not "changed" nor "changes"
# Wrap at 72 characters
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# <footer>
# List any breaking changes or issues closed by this commit
# 
# BREAKING CHANGE: <description>
# Closes #<issue-number>
# 
# Signed-off-by: Your Name <your.email@example.com>
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Remember to:
#   - Use imperative mood in subject and body
#   - Limit subject line to 72 characters
#   - Reference issues and breaking changes
#   - Sign-off your commits with DCO
# 
# Types:
#   feat:     A new feature
#   fix:      A bug fix
#   docs:     Documentation only changes
#   style:    Formatting, missing semi-colons, etc (no code change)
#   refactor: Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   perf:     Code change that improves performance
#   test:     Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
#   build:    Changes that affect the build system or dependencies
#   ci:       Changes to CI configuration files and scripts
#   chore:    Other changes that don't modify src or test files
#   revert:   Reverts a previous commit
#
# Scopes:
#   operator:    Changes to the operator core
#   api:         Changes to the API server
#   ui:          Changes to the React UI
#   controllers: Changes to Kubernetes controllers
#   crd:         Changes to Custom Resource Definitions
#   webhooks:    Changes to admission/validation webhooks
#   helm:        Changes to Helm charts
#   docs:        Changes to documentation
#   deps:        Dependency updates
#   security:    Security-related changes
#
# Examples:
#   feat(operator): add prometheus scrape interval configuration
#   fix(api): correct platform status endpoint response
#   docs(operator): update installation instructions for v2.0
#   perf(controllers): optimize reconciliation loop for large clusters
